<P>
   (NYT41) CLEVELAND -- Oct. 11, 1999 -- BBA-REDSOX-INDIANS-8,
10-11 -- Pitcher Pedro Martinez of the Boston Red Sox celebrates
his team's victory over the Cleveland Indians in the fifth and
deciding game of the American League Divisional Playoffs on Monday.
Boston came back from an 0-2 game deficit to win the best-of-five
series. (Barry Chin/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT40) CLEVELAND -- Oct. 11, 1999 -- BBA-REDSOX-INDIANS-7,
10-11 -- Pedro Martinez of the Boston Red Sox covers first base as
Kenny Lofton of the Cleveland Indians slides head-first into the
bag in the fifth and deciding game of the American League
Divisional Playoffs on Monday. Lofton dislocated his left shoulder
during this play and was replaced in center field in the top of the
fifth inning by Dave Roberts with the score tied at 8-8. (Jim
Davis/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT39) CLEVELAND -- Oct. 11, 1999 -- BBA-REDSOX-INDIANS-6,
10-11 -- Troy O'Leary of the Boston Red Sox watches the flight of
the ball as he hits a grand slam home run against the Cleveland
Indians in the fifth and deciding game of the American League
Divisional Playoffs on Monday. (Jim Davis/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT38) CLEVELAND -- Oct. 11, 1999 -- BBA-REDSOX-INDIANS-5,
10-11 -- Kenny Lofton of the Cleveland Indians fails to retrieve a
two-run home run by Nomar Garciaparra of the Boston Red Sox in the
first inning of the fifth and deciding game of the American League
Divisional Playoffs on Monday. Lofton later dislocated his left
shoulder and was replaced in center field in the top of the fifth
by Dave Roberts with the score tied at 8-8. (Jim Davis/Boston Globe
Photo)
</P>
