<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-12 00:09 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3945 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN-(SLAN     10-12 0308
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FARMER CHOOSES USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC received one of its highest-profile basketball
commitments in years Monday night when shooting guard Desmon Farmer
selected the Trojans over Marquette.
</P>
<P>
   Farmer (6-foot-4, 195 pounds), who plays for Northwestern High
School in Flint, Mich., was rated the No. 2 shooting guard in the
country last spring by recruiting-analyst Bob Gibbons. He was rated
the 24th-best prospect overall in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is one of the top pure shooters in the country,'' Gibbons
said. ``He could step in and have a chance to be Freshman of the
Year in the Pac-10. This clearly is an impact recruit for (USC
coach) Henry Bibby.''
</P>
<P>
   Farmer's stock fell when he injured his knee and missed last
summer's camps and tournaments. Farmer said he tore the upper part
of his anterior cruciate ligament but that it was less severe than
normal ACL injuries and he will play for his high school team this
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm back playing already,'' he said. ``This is my last month
of rehabilitation. A lot of schools backed down. USC stayed with
me. I feel comfortable around the coaches and the players. I can
get my degree and get to the NBA.''
</P>
<P>
   Farmer was also being recruited by Michigan, Syracuse and New
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Farmer averaged 20.3 points and 7.9 rebounds last season. He
plays at the same high school as former USC shooting guard Anthony
Pendleton, who played for the Trojans in 1988-89.
</P>
<P>
   USC remains in the running for two other high-profile players:
6-10 forward Jared Jeffries, rated the No. 7 player in the country
by Gibbons, is down to Duke, Indiana and the Trojans. And last
weekend, 6-9 forward Herve Lamizana, among the top 30 players in
the country, visited USC.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-12-99 0009EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
