<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-12 00:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3958 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r i BC-LA-DALAI-LAMA-LADN     10-12 0380
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LA-DALAI-LAMA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DALAI LAMA HONORS WORKERS FOR FREEDOM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY ROBERT MONROE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Dalai Lama's message to a packed audience at
the Stephen S. Wise Temple was as constant and humble as his
trademark maroon and saffron robes, even in the midst of opulence
and celebrity.
</P>
<P>
   The spiritual leader of Tibet _ and the movement to free it _
told the audience to keep up the support that might end Chinese
occupation of his country.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe that support and speaking on behalf of people who
suffer injustice is, in fact, the practice and essence of
spirituality,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   On the second day of a four-day tour of the Los Angeles area,
the Dalai Lama presented Light of Truth awards to three recipients
for their work toward the freeing of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
   He drew the spectrum of his American admirers _ limousines and
luxury cars mixed with older-model compacts with ``Free Tibet''
stickers outside the temple.
</P>
<P>
   Bell Canyon resident Ken Greenberg likened the Dalai Lama's
presence to what must have been commanded by Mohandas K. Gandhi,
the Indian independence leader.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the nice thing is he doesn't have to say too much. I
think the medium is the message,'' Greenberg said.
</P>
<P>
   The Light of Truth Award has been given annually to celebrities
such as Martin Scorsese and Richard Gere and activists for their
work publicizing Tibet's plight.
</P>
<P>
   This year, the recipients included American Himalayan founder
Richard Blum, Hugh Richardson, the only Western diplomat in Tibet
from 1936 to 1947 and Danielle Mitterand, widow of the former
French president and leader of her own human rights organization.
</P>
<P>
   She was introduced by actress Sharon Stone at the Monday night
event attended by Rev. Jesse Jackson and former Vice President
Walter Mondale.
</P>
<P>
   After the awards, Blum expressed the same optimism as the Dalai
Lama that their goal is coming closer to fruition.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't see it yet but there's a real internal struggle
going on (in the Chinese government),'' Blum said. ``But the
hard-liners still have the upper hand.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dalai Lama is scheduled to speak Wednesday as part of
Pasadena's Distinguished Speaker Series.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-12-99 0050EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
