<SLUG> BC-TIME-WARNER-EARNINGS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIME WARNER TO REPORT RISE IN PROFITS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DAVE McNARY  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Media giant Time Warner Inc. is expected to
report sharply improved third-quarter earnings Wednesday despite a
significant downturn in its music business.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts surveyed by First Call Corp. expect Time Warner to
report profits of 5 cents a share, compared with a loss of 6 cents
a share in the year-ago period. Schroder &AMP; Co. has projected cash
flow -- reflecting profits before interest, taxes and amortization
and a key measure for debt-heavy companies like Time Warner -- will
rise 3.7 percent to $1.12 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Basic cable operations, including TBS, TNT, CNN and the Cartoon
Network, should continue to generate impressive results with cash
flow gains around 20 percent. Strong ratings have enabled networks
to boost advertising rates.
</P>
<P>
   Premium cable networks HBO and Cinemax, cable systems and
publishing operations will post cash-flow gains around 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts are less enthusiastic about filmed entertainment, which
includes TV production, and forecasts range from a small decline in
cash flow to single-digit gains. Syndication revenues from
``E.R.,'' ``Friends,'' ``The Rosie O'Donnell Show'' and ``The Drew
Carey Show'' should boost results. But Warner Bros. and New Line
movies have been lackluster, including ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' ``Mickey
Blue Eyes,'' ``Detroit Rock City,'' ``Chill Factor'' and ``Iron
Giant.''
</P>
<P>
   Music cash flow could decline by more than 20 percent due partly
to softness in key foreign markets.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner stock has risen more than 200 percent in the last
four years and peaked at $78.25 in April. It closed Monday down
$1.50 at $63.813 despite a ``buy'' rating from Jeffries &AMP; Co.,
which began coverage with an $85 target for the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner, which has extensive operations at Warner Bros. in
Burbank, is expected to release the earnings report before the
market opens Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
