   PERSONAL FINANCE
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ The federal retirement system is coming to
your mailbox, and it wants to help. No kidding: In the next year,
most American workers over 25 will get an individual estimate of
how much retirement money to expect from Social Security. It's the
Social Security Administration's way of telling you what to expect
_ and what to worry about _ as you plan your retirement. (Ezell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   LILY-TOMLIN _ Growing up in Detroit in the early '50s,
precocious Mary Jean Tomlin loved to put on shows, imitating the
female stars she would see on the television set her blue-collar
family could barely afford. By the end of the '60s, she was a
sensation on national television on Rowan &AMP; Martin's Laugh-In,
adopting her mother's first name and amusing the country with such
acutely observed, comically exaggerated characters as telephone
operator martinet Ernestine and a philosophical, smart-mouthed
5-year-old named Edith Ann. Now she brings her characters with her
on the road. (Palm Beach Post). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TOMLIN-MOVIES _ Soon after her days on ``Laugh-In,'' Lily Tomlin
made the transition to film. Some of her thoughts on her movie
roles. (Palm Beach Post). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   FENG-SHUI _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ In case you've missed the
feng shui bandwagon, it is, according to Webster's, ``a Chinese
geomantic practice in which a structure or site is chosen or
configured so as to harmonize with the spiritual forces that
inhabit it; also: auspicious orientation, placement or arrangement
as determined by feng shui.'' In other words, the way your house
sits on its lot, the direction the doors face, where you put your
furniture, where you hang your art, what kinds of symbolic
decorations and colors you use _ all of these things, and more _
can affect your moods, health, relationships and financial success.
Feng shui has been around for more than 3,000 years, but its
burgeoning popularity in the West, experts say, is a side effect of
our hectic, stressed lives. (Graulich, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FENG-SHUI-SIDEBAR _ Tips on finding the right feng shui
consultant. (Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FENG-SHUI-CARDS _ Mae Chin Williams, a feng shui consultant
based in Ohio, has reduced the 3,000-year-old Chinese art of
placement into a 65-card deck called the Feng Shui Card System. If
you can play Go Fish, Mae Chin promises, you can feng shui your
home or office in a jif. (Graulich, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FENG-SHUI-TIPS _ The Chinese art of feng shui is more than 3,000
years old, and trying to figure out all its symbols and meanings
sometimes feels like it might take that long. We asked several
local feng shui consultants to boil it down. (Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
