governing trade body, local leaders were exultant. But it is
increasingly clear that the largest free-trade meeting ever held in
this country has also become a giant protest magnet for a broad
array of environmental, labor and other groups that say the trade
body is a hand-maid to corporate interests whose authority should
be sharply curtailed. By Sam Herhovek.
</P>
