<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ADVISORY-AIDS-SERIES-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ATTN EDITORS:  

</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AIDS IN AFRICA
</P>
<P>
   AIDS is ravaging sub-Sahara Africa, where last year 2 million
people died of the disease and some 22.5 million people now carry
HIV. In a four-part series, the Globe examines the horrific reality
of the situation, including how people are coping with life in the
land of the dead and dying. &UR;  &LR; The series will move Wednesday, early
p.m., for immediate release.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
