<P>
   CHINA-POPULATION _ BEIJING _ On the day the world population
officially reached six billion, China confounded speculation
Tuesday that it might relax its one-child policy and pledged a new
``historical leap'' to further restrict its birth rate. Meeting at
the Great Hall of the People on Tiananmen Square, officials of the
world's most populous country said the next leap in birth control
would be an attempt to bring a zero growth in China's population by
the mid-21st century. Their objective is stabilize China's
population at 1.6 billion people in around 2045, by which time
India will have become the most populous nation on the globe.
(Kunstel/Albright, Cox News Service). 20.
