halting the smuggling of looted antiquities from Italy into
America. Coming on the heels of three major raids against
antiquities dealers in Italy, the request seeks import restrictions
on a range of treasures, art and artifacts representing more than
5,000 years of history. A State Department review of the request in
Washingon Tuesday drew harsh criticism from art dealers and museum
curators, while archaeologists contended the action is needed to
halt the market-driven demand for looted treasures. (Toner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
