   PAKISTAN-COUP (New Dehli, India) _ Developments. Hours after
Pakistan's prime minister fired the powerful army chief, the army
struck back with a swift, decisive coup. Troops surrounded the
prime minister's home, closed airports and took state-run
television off the air. By Celia Dugger. (We plan to move the story
by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
