evidence shows that smoking causes lung cancer and other deadly
diseases, after decades of disputing the findings of the surgeon
general and other medical authorities. On a new Internet site it is
unveiling at midnight, the company will state that there is an
overwhelming medical and scientific consensus that cigarette
smoking causes diseases including lung cancer, emphysema and heart
disease. By Barry Meier. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in
``a'' news file.) 1,100 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIRTH-PAIN (Undated) _ More and more women are deciding that
labor pain is a rite of passage they can do without, and are
gratefully accepting pain medicine during childbirth, doctors
report at an anesthesiology conference in Dallas. But the trend
troubles some who say that young women are missing out on one of
life's great transforming experiences and needlessly exposing
themselves and their babies to the side effects of anesthetic
drugs. By Denise Grady. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``a''
