   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-CHAMBERLAIN (Los Angeles) _ Wilt Chamberlain, one of the
most dominant players in the history of basketball, died Tuesday at
63. By Frank Litsky. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   With column, reaction stories and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   MENTALLY-ILL-VOTE (Undated) _ On the morning of the 1996
presidential election, Sharon Denny drove to her polling place, an
elementary school in her neighborhood in Houston. But standing in
line, Ms. Denny, who is 51 and has suffered from manic-depression
for 35 years, broke into a cold sweat before returning home, her
ballot uncast, as it has been in every election since she first
registered to vote 15 years ago. In next year's presidential
election, however, Ms. Denny knows that she will finally vote
because of the Mental Health Voter Empowerment Project, an effort
to create a nationwide constituency of people with mental illness
and make sure they get to the polls on Election Day 2000. By Erica
Goode. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 2,200
words.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
