<P>
   COURT-NICHOLS (Washington) _ The Supreme Court rejects the
appeal of convicted Oklahoma City bomber Terry Nichols that his
federal conviction for conspiring to use weapons of mass
destruction should be overturned because he never intended to hurt
anyone. The action let stand the life sentence given to Nichols,
44, for his involvement in the 1995 attack that killed 168 people.
By MARK HELM. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ With the official embrace of the
AFL-CIO, the scary roller-coaster that is the campaign of Vice
President Al Gore now moves up. But with Bill Bradley closing in on
him, Gore's momentum is sure to dip again before the ride is over.
My money is still on Gore to get the Democratic nomination, but
he's having to work for it. By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
</P>
