<SLUG> BC-TIME-MULLIN-UCLA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UCLA GRADUATE SCHOOL TO GET BIG DONATION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY GREGORY J. WILCOX  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Peter W. Mullin, a Los Angeles entrepreneur and
philanthropist, is donating $5 million to the John E. Anderson
Graduate School of Management at UCLA, officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Mullin's donation will fund a chair and faculty research
projects on a wide range of business issues, said Bruce Willison,
dean of the Anderson School.
</P>
<P>
   The school is ranked among the top 10 graduate business programs
in the world.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's a very, very nice gift,'' he said. ``This is a powerful
statement of Peter's belief in the future of the Anderson School
and in the promise of the vital research done by our faculty.''
</P>
<P>
   Mullin, who owns a firm that focuses on insurance and executive
compensation issues, attended the University of California, Los
Angeles for a year and became interested in the Anderson School
because of its work in the field of entrepreneurship.
</P>
<P>
   ``One thing leads to another. You give, then you want to get
more involved. You get more involved, and you want to give,''
Mullin said in a statement. ``I truly believe the Anderson School
is one of the finest management-education institutions in the
world. I want to do what I can to ensure that continues to be
true.''
</P>
<P>
   Mullin's gift will pay for the ``Peter W. Mullin Endowed Fund
for Faculty Excellence.'' The school is also renaming its
Anderson's Management Commons building the Mullin Management
Commons.
</P>
<P>
   Mullin supports a variety of charitable causes, particularly
those related to education in the Los Angeles area.
</P>
<P>
   A graduate of the University of California, Santa Barbara, he
founded Mullin Consulting Inc. in 1969. He also co-founded
Strategic Compensation Associates and M Financial Holding Co.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
