on Tuesday after signing a new law that makes New Jersey the fourth
state in the nation to prohibit the sale of new handguns unless it
is accompanied by a trigger lock. Standing from left are
Assemblymen Alfred Steele, Tom Smith, and Guy Talarice. (Laura
Pedrick/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) UNDATED -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- SPY-SATELLITE-PHOTOS-B&AMP;W,
10-12 -- Inaugurating a new commercial era, Space Imaging Inc., a
private company based in Thornton, Colo., made this photo public on
Tuesday which shows the White House. The image, taken from space,
was cropped from a wider image. Photos at this resolution are the
world's first being made available from a commercial satellite
whose sharpness rivals those of military spies in the sky. (Space
Imaging/New York Times Photo)
</P>
