<P>
   (NYT33) ATLANTA -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-2, 10-12 --
Atlanta Braves pitcher Greg Maddux fires one at New York Mets John
Olerud in the first inning in Game 1 of the National League
Championship Series on Tuesday at Turner Field. (Rich
Addicks/Atlanta Journal-Constitution) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) WESTLAKE VILLAGE, Calif. -- Oct. 12, 1999 --
SCHOOLS-VIOLENCE, 10-12 -- At a workshop on crisis response teams
last month Ronald Stephens, left, executive director of the
National School Safety Center, an expert on school violence, talked
with Linda Drager of Springfield, Ill., a participant. Schools,
Stephens says, remain relatively safe. One of his favorite
statistics, which he often uses in conversations, is that young
people are 99 times more likely to be shot and killed on the street
or at home than in school -- a figure that may bring cold comfort
to worried parents. (Kim Kulish/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) ATLANTA -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-1, 10-12 --
New York Mets coach Dave Wallace, left, speaks to pitcher Masato
Yoshii, center, as catcher Mike Piazza looks on after Yoshii gave
up the first run of the game in the first inning on Tuesday against
the Atlanta Braves in Game 1 of the National League Championship
Series. (Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) ASHKELON, Israel -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- ISRAEL-CUBANS,
10-12 -- In Ashkelon, Irolando Carpio, left, and Zeida Quintera
dance to music on a videotape they brought from Cuba. It has been a
year since their extended family of nine left Cuba. But until
Monday, Carpio and Ms. Quintero - and 400 other Cuban immigrants -
were an Israeli state secret. Few knew that Cubans have been
trickling into Ben-Gurion Airport in Tel Aviv since 1995, from
Havana by way of Paris. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) WILMINGTON, Del. -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- DUPONT-Y2K, 10-12
-- Cinda Hallman displays a watch that was given to a top performer
in her Year 2000 project at DuPont. As chief information officer of
DuPont in 1995, Hallman sounded the Y2K alarm in the top reaches of
management. She then created an organization that mapped DuPont's
vulnerability to the problem and developed performance benchmarks
to hold managers' feet to the fire when their groups lagged behind.
(Tim Shaffer/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) WILMINGTON, N.C.-- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BKO-JORDAN-VISIT-2,
10-12 --Michael Jordan compares hand size with Bert Pickett a
Pender High School while the retired all-star basketball player was
signing autographs on Tuesday. Jordan, who played high school
basketball in the neighboring county, came to the school inspire
hope to some three dozen high school students whose families had
lost everything to the extensive flooding caused by Hurricane
Floyd. (Mark Courtney/Wilmington Star-News)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) WILMINGTON, N.C.-- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BKO-JORDAN-VISIT-1,
10-12 --Michael Jordan gets a hug from a student at Pender High
School during a visit to the school on Tuesday. Jordan, who played
high school basketball in the neighboring county, came to inspire
some hope to some three dozen high school students whose families
had lost everything to the extensive flooding caused by Hurricane
Floyd. (Mark Courtney/Wilmington Star-News)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BBA-YANKEES-REDSOX-3, 10-12
-- Pedro and Ramon Martinez of the Boston Red Sox take a walk in
the outfield at Yankee Stadium on Tuesday during a team practice
session. The Red Sox face the New York Yankees at the stadium on
Wednesday in Game 1 of the American League Championship Series.
(Bill Greene/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) NEW YORK -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BBA-YANKEES-REDSOX-2, 10-12
-- From left, Donnie Sadler, clowns with Boston Red Sox teammates
Troy O'Leary and Pat Rapp during practice session at Yankee Stadium
on Tuesday. The Red Sox face the New York Yankees at the stadium on
Wednesday in Game 1 of the American League Championship Series.
(Bill Greene/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) NEW YORK -- Oct. 12, 1999 -- BBA-YANKEES-REDSOX, 10-12
-- Boston Red Sox pitcher Pedro Martinez signs autographs in the
