<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UTILITIES-MERGER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CON ED IS SAID TO BE BUYING NORTHEAST FOR $3.29 BILLION 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: N.Y., Conn., Northeast points)  (Eds: This story was added to the New York Times business front
page) 
(af) 
 By AGIS SALPUKAS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Consolidated Edison Inc. agreed Tuesday night to buy
Northeast Utilities for $3.29 billion in cash and stock, according
to people close to the talks, in a deal that could eventually bring
cheaper power to its customers.
</P>
<P>
   Under terms of the deal, which the boards of both companies
approved Tuesday, Con Edison, which is based in Manhattan, will pay
$25 a share in cash and stock for the outstanding shares of
Northeast, which is based in Berlin, Conn. Another $1 a share will
be paid if units 2 and 3 of Northeast's Millstone nuclear plant in
Connecticut are sold.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Northeast Utilities rose 12.5 cents Tuesday, to
$21.25, while Con Edison fell 75 cents, to $36.4375. Based on
Northeast's closing price, the deal represents a 17.6 percent
premium.
</P>
<P>
   The deal is the biggest move by Con Edison so far to protect its
base of three million customers, who are being courted by outsiders
to buy power at lower rates as New York deregulates its utility
market. Con Edison will raise its customer base to 4.7 million and
extend its reach as far north as New Hampshire.
</P>
<P>
   It is also a move to become more competitive. Northeast has been
aggressively preparing for deregulation in Connecticut,
Massachusetts and New Hampshire. Though Northeast had to spin off
its power plants as part of the deregulation, it has bought plants
and built up a source of cheap power, which Con Edison could sell
to its customers, possibly lowering their rates eventually.
Northeast has also built up an organization to market that power
throughout the region.
</P>
<P>
   The people close to the deal said the two utilities expected
savings of $1.3 billion to $1.4 billion in the next 10 years.
Whether there will be layoffs has yet to be determined, the people
said.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-12-99 2159EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
