<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-PAKISTAN-COUP-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Despite all my advices, they tried to interfere with the armed
forces, the last remaining viable institution in which all of you
take so much pride and look up to at all times for stability, unity
and integrity of our beloved country.''
</P>
<P>
   _GEN. PERVEZ MUSHARRAF, addressing Pakistanis after ousting the
prime minister and his government.
</P>
