Bruce Ritter, who founded a shelter for runaways in 1969 and then
resigned under pressure as its president in 1990 after being
accused of financial and sexual improprieties, died Thursday at his
farmhouse near Decatur, N.Y. He was 72. Ritter is seen in a 1981
file photo. (New York Times Photo)
